Time to First Working (Requirements to first runnable outcome) 1 – 2.5 hours

Total Dev Time (Requirement -> code completed -> PR) 1.5 – 3.5 hours

Time spent per phase:

Requirement clarification: 30 mins – 2 hours (Includes detailed Spec/Prompt writing)

Implementation: ~30 mins

Fixing Bugs/Rework: 15 – 30 mins

Testing/Validation: 15 – 30 mins

Number of iterations before "Acceptable" (how many times if any code was revised after inital implementation) 2 – 3 times

Time per change (Small change -> how long to implement + test) Fast (< 5 mins)

Bug Categories:

Logic Errors: Near 0 (Rare)

Missed Requirements: Common (Due to prompt omissions)

Config/integration errors: Low

Regression Issue (Did change break existing functionality): Occasional risk

Time Spent Debugging Low

Bus Factor (If primary Dev is out, how long does it take someone else to take over?) High (The Spec file acts as immediate documentation for others)

Documentation Quality High (The Spec itself serves as the documentation)

Consistency in implementation High

Manual Testing Reduced (Agent can often generate test scripts)

Effort Split (% coding vs rework) 60% Spec Writing & Reqs / 20% Implementation / 20% Fixes
